The paper deals with the problem of estimating 3D hand meshes from single RGB images, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of a differentiable renderer and a neural network, which are techniques commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of self-data augmentation, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
